import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['miles'] = pd.to_numeric(data['miles'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='miles', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['miles'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gas_per_mile'] = data['gas'] / data['miles']
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='miles', y='gas_per_mile', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['gas_per_mile'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['gas_per_mile'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average amount of gas used per mile?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='miles', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['miles'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Miles Driven')
    plt.title('What is the trend in miles driven over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
